html#S2\">S2</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.html#is_s2","kind":"def","line":36,"name":"is_s2","sourceLink":"https://github.com/aetilley/banach-tarski/blob/a920deea0a3f3207049f8201fc1e7a0bb8cf4c93/BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.lean#L36-L44"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.html#to_s2_r3\"><span class=\"name\">to_s2_r3</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.html#IccT\">IccT</a> → <a href=\"./BanachTarski/Common.html#R3\">R3</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.html#to_s2_r3","kind":"def","line":34,"name":"to_s2_r3","sourceLink":"https://github.com/aetilley/banach-tarski/blob/a920deea0a3f3207049f8201fc1e7a0bb8cf4c93/BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.lean#L34-L34"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.html#interval_uncountable\"><span class=\"name\">interval_uncountable</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Countable/Defs.html#Uncountable\">Uncountable</a> <a href=\"./BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.html#IccT\">IccT</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.html#interval_uncountable","kind":"instance","line":27,"name":"interval_uncountable","sourceLink":"https://github.com/aetilley/banach-tarski/blob/a920deea0a3f3207049f8201fc1e7a0bb8cf4c93/BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.lean#L27-L32"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.html#IccT\"><span class=\"name\">IccT</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Here we define `orbit`, the `Bad` set, and the parametrized families `rot` and `rot_iso`\n(defined and developed in the module Rot.lean) and `skew_rot`\nCrucially we prove that there are only countably many \"Bad\" \"rot\"s and \"skew_rot\"s.\nWe work with `rot_iso` whenever possible, and only convert to a statement about `rot`\nat the end (using the `same_action` lemma).\n\nWe also define as well as some geometric objects used by the main theorems\nlike ball and cone, and the group G3 of isometries.\n\nWe also prove some \"obvious\" things like that SO(3) is contained in G3 (the group of isometries)\nand some lemmas about cardinality of sets. ","docLink":"./BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.html#IccT","kind":"def","line":7,"name":"IccT","sourceLink":"https://github.com/aetilley/banach-tarski/blob/a920deea0a3f3207049f8201fc1e7a0bb8cf4c93/BanachTarski/GeometricUtils.lean#L7-L25"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib","BanachTarski.Common","BanachTarski.Rot"],"instances":[{"className":"Uncountable","name":"interval_uncountable","typeNames":["IccT"]},{"className":"MulAction","name":"instMulActionG3R3","typeNames":["G3","R3"]},{"className":"SMulCommClass","name":"instSMulCommClassRealSubtypeMatrixFinOfNatNatMemSubmonoidSO3R3","typeNames":["Real","Subtype","R3"]}],"name":"BanachTarski.GeometricUtils"}